<p><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-weight: bold;">How long will this program take?</span></p>
<p>Our online degree program allows students the flexibility to finish their degree while balancing a busy life. Students can accelerate to graduation by taking courses year round or take a semester off when needed. Students must complete the program within eight years.</p>
<h3>What are the courses like?</h3>
<p>Online Courses at BYU-Idaho follow a similar format and have the same learning objectives as campus-based courses. Students should expect to interact with each other and participate in the learning model. <a href="x21934.xml">Learn more about BYU-Idaho courses online.</a></p>
<h3>Where do I begin?</h3>
<p>Students who meet the <a href="x24381.xml">admission requirements</a> can apply to be directly admitted into an online degree program. These students will start by taking the online orientation course,&nbsp;<a href="x43378.xml">GS 111</a>. This is a one-credit course offered every block that prepares students to succeed online and charts a course to graduation. Pathway students who complete Academic Start do not need to take GS 111.</p>
